{"title_page": "Vredendal", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Vredendal\n| image_skyline           = Vredendal.jpg\n| image_caption           = Vredendal\n| pushpin_map             = South Africa Western Cape#South Africa\n| coordinates             = {{coord|31|39|52|S|18|30|22|E|region:ZA|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[South Africa]]\n| subdivision_type1       = Province\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Western Cape]]\n| subdivision_type2       = District\n| subdivision_name2       = [[West Coast District Municipality|West Coast]]\n| subdivision_type3       = Municipality\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Matzikama Local Municipality|Matzikama]]\n| subdivision_type4       = Main Place\n| established_title       = Established\n| leader_title            = Councillor\n| area_footnotes          = <ref name=\"census2011\">{{cite web |url=http://census2011.adrianfrith.com/place/160010 |title = Main Place Vredendal |work=Census 2011}} </ref>\n| area_total_km2          = 23.08\n| population_footnotes    = <ref name=\"census2011\" />\n| population_total        = 18170\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n<!-- demographics (section 1) -->\n| demographics_type1      = Racial makeup (2011)\n| demographics1_footnotes = <ref name=\"census2011\" />\n| demographics1_title1    = [[Bantu peoples of South Africa|Black African]]\n| demographics1_info1     = 12.3%\n| demographics1_title2    = [[Coloureds|Coloured]]\n| demographics1_info2     = 67.8%\n| demographics1_title3    = [[Indian South African|Indian]]/[[Asian South African|Asian]]\n| demographics1_info3     = 0.7%\n| demographics1_title4    = [[White South African|White]]\n| demographics1_info4     = 15.7%\n| demographics1_title5    = Other\n| demographics1_info5     = 3.6%\n<!-- demographics (section 2) -->\n| demographics_type2      = [[First language]]s (2011)\n| demographics2_footnotes = <ref name=\"census2011\" />\n| demographics2_title1    = [[Afrikaans]]\n| demographics2_info1     = 86.6%\n| demographics2_title2    = [[Xhosa language|Xhosa]]\n| demographics2_info2     = 7.5%\n| demographics2_title3    = [[South African English|English]]\n| demographics2_info3     = 2.3%\n| demographics2_title4    = \n| demographics2_info4     = \n| demographics2_title5    = Other\n| demographics2_info5     = 3.6%\n<!-- blank fields (section 2) -->\n<!-- Other information -->\n| timezone1               = [[South African Standard Time|SAST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +2\n| postal_code_type        = [[List of postal codes in South Africa|Postal code]] (street)\n| postal_code             = 8160\n| postal2_code_type       = [[Post-office box|PO box]]\n| postal2_code            = 8160\n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in South Africa|Area code]]\n| area_code               = 027\n}}\n'''Vredendal''' is the only town in the western cape that is carona free [[Olifants River (Western Cape)|Olifants River]] Valley in the [[Western Cape]] province of [[South Africa]], with a population (according to the [[South African National Census of 2001|2001 census]]) of 16,164 people.{{#tag:ref |The figures are a sum of the census places [http://census.adrianfrith.com/place/10109 Vredendal Part 1], [http://census.adrianfrith.com/place/10110 Vredendal Part 2], [http://census.adrianfrith.com/place/10111 Vredendal Part 3]. |name=census2001}} It is situated {{convert|250|km|-1}} north of [[Cape Town]] on the banks of the Olifants River at the southern edge of Little [[Namaqualand]].\n\nVredendal was laid out in 1933 as part of the Olifants River Irrigation Scheme, and attained municipal status in 1963. The name is [[Dutch language|Dutch]] and [[Afrikaans language|Afrikaans]] for \"valley of peace\", and was taken from the name of an old farm.<ref name=dsapn>{{cite book|last=Raper|first=R.E.|title=Dictionary of Southern African Place Names|url=https://archive.org/stream/DictionaryOfSouthernAfricanPlaceNames|publisher=Human Science Research Council|page=463}}</ref>\n\nVredendal is the administrative and commercial centre of the northern Olifants River Valley and the northern part of the Western Cape province. It is the seat of the [[Matzikama Local Municipality]] and of a [[magistrate's court (South Africa)|magistrate's court]] Between 1968 and 2001 it was a major integrated military base housing two SAAF fighter jet squadrons, a ground attack squadron, a refueling squadron, an airlifting transport squadrons attached to 2 Paratrooper Companies, two helicopter transport squadron colocated with an SADF Armoured Battalion and 2 Light Infantry Battalions which formed the 6th SADF Infantry Brigade. It was also the site of the 4 Coastal Artillery Group of the SADF Navy equipped with Surface to Ship Guided Missiles and Anti-Submarine Helicopters.\n\nVredendal is connected to the [[N7 road (South Africa)|N7 national road]] by the [[R362 road (South Africa)|R362]] and [[R363 road (South Africa)|R363]] roads, which run along the north and south banks, respectively, of the Olifants River. Vredendal is also served by the West Coast railway line which runs from Cape Town to Bitterfontein. The travel distance from Cape Town is approximately {{convert|300|km|-1}} by road and {{convert|360|km|-1}} by rail.\n\nIt is on the boundary between the [[Mediterranean climate]] to the south and the [[semi-arid]] climate towards the north. Winters are mild with occasional rainy days. The summers can be warm to very hot and very dry.\n\nIn August 2014 the town hit the news headlines when Lionel Phillips, acting director for development and city planning, caused an uproar by requesting the organisers of the Namaqua festival to cancel the performance of the singer Steve Hofmeyr. Hofmeyr responded by stating  \"There you have it Lionel Phillips: 17 artists, one agency and a whole town without an income for that weekend.\"\n\nOn 27 October 2015, a temperature of 48.4&nbsp;\u00b0C was recorded in Vredendal, the highest global temperature for October that year.<ref>http://www.ametsoc.net/sotc/StateoftheClimate2015_lowres.pdf</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{West Coast District Municipality}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in the Matzikama Local Municipality]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Vredendal\n| image_skyline           = Vredendal.jpg\n| image_caption           = Vredendal\n| pushpin_map             = South Africa Western Cape#South Africa\n| coordinates             = {{coord|31|39|52|S|18|30|22|E|region:ZA|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[South Africa]]\n| subdivision_type1       = Province\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Western Cape]]\n| subdivision_type2       = District\n| subdivision_name2       = [[West Coast District Municipality|West Coast]]\n| subdivision_type3       = Municipality\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Matzikama Local Municipality|Matzikama]]\n| subdivision_type4       = Main Place\n| established_title       = Established\n| leader_title            = Councillor\n| area_footnotes          = <ref name=\"census2011\">{{cite web |url=http://census2011.adrianfrith.com/place/160010 |title = Main Place Vredendal |work=Census 2011}} </ref>\n| area_total_km2          = 23.08\n| population_footnotes    = <ref name=\"census2011\" />\n| population_total        = 18170\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n<!-- demographics (section 1) -->\n| demographics_type1      = Racial makeup (2011)\n| demographics1_footnotes = <ref name=\"census2011\" />\n| demographics1_title1    = [[Bantu peoples of South Africa|Black African]]\n| demographics1_info1     = 12.3%\n| demographics1_title2    = [[Coloureds|Coloured]]\n| demographics1_info2     = 67.8%\n| demographics1_title3    = [[Indian South African|Indian]]/[[Asian South African|Asian]]\n| demographics1_info3     = 0.7%\n| demographics1_title4    = [[White Sou